gmd:description.gco:CharacterString:
All  NUTS 2006 feature classes were based on common repository coverages. These are collections of geometry from different sources which contain all geometry necessary to created the different feature classes for the datasets COMM, NUTS, CNTR and COAS. The creation of the common repository coverage is a complex process with a lot of manual handling. Here only the process steps after the creation of the common repository are briefly described:


Step 1: The first step was to create an empty database schema for the NUTS_2006 dataset;


Step 2: Pre-processing coverage data to prepare them to load into the new Geodatabase structure which included: 
       (i) clean coverages with correct precision + check for labelerrors;
       (ii) creating regions for the NUTS level (to match subtypes in the GDB);
       (iii) add a merge item to the boundary feature class and dissolve to remove pseudonodes;
       (iv) derivation of a table that defines relationship between boundaries and regions based on spatial relation;
       (v) attribute manipulation to match the new structure;


Step 3: the preprocessed feature classes were loaded in the empty geodatabase schema for the NUTS_2006 dataset;


Step 4: adding metadata
